---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
---

<Base title="Rathaus Oberägeri" description="Carbon-reduction analysis of the Rathaus building in Oberägeri, Canton Zug.">

  <Hero
    eyebrow="Sustainable Operations Management · 2026"
    title="Carbon-reduction<br/>analysis of the<br/><em>Rathaus Oberägeri</em>"
    subtitle="A study of the building's energy use, costs and CO₂ footprint — and the rooftop solar levers that could shrink them."
    image="/67b84a4ecef4e.jpeg"
    imageAlt="Rathaus Oberägeri"
    authors="Valentin Nägeli · Ellette Sidler-Dever · Jan-Akim A. Reimer&#10;University of Zurich"
  />

  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="overview">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="overview-inner reveal">
        <div class="overview-label">Overview</div>
        <div class="overview-body">
          <p class="overview-text">
            This project evaluates how the Oberägeri town hall can reduce its operational carbon footprint while maintaining economic responsibility and service continuity. Using audited electricity, heat, and hot water data, our project establishes a verified 2025 energy and CO₂ baseline. This baseline reflects the building's real consumption patterns — specifically its dependence on district heat, grid electricity, and diesel emergency generation. From this baseline, the analysis assesses the technical and financial viability of rooftop photovoltaic systems and solar thermal integration. This assessment draws on research about Swiss regulatory frameworks, <em>Energiestadt</em> priorities, and technical aspects of PV panels, solar thermal systems, and alternative generator solutions.
          </p>
          <p class="overview-text">
            The core contribution of the project is a scenario-based carbon reduction model that quantifies how different solar configurations influence emissions, lifecycle costs, and long-horizon financial outcomes. These scenarios are implemented in an interactive calculator that computes the optimum system size and technology mix for the town hall. The optimum identified in the results section reflects the configuration that minimises CO₂ emissions while meeting municipal budget thresholds and achieving the strongest economic performance over the 25-year evaluation period.
          </p>
          <p class="overview-text">
            Together, the baseline assessment and optimised scenario modelling provide a clear roadmap for how Oberägeri can align its administrative operations with its climate commitments. The findings offer a replicable framework for other municipalities seeking to reduce emissions through targeted, data-grounded investments in rooftop solar infrastructure.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick chapter index -->
  <section class="chapter-index">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="grid">
        <a href="/chapter-4" class="card tilt-card reveal reveal-delay-1" data-astro-prefetch>
          <div class="card-glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <span class="n">04</span>
          <h3 class="serif">Literature Review</h3>
          <p>Swiss energy policy, public-building efficiency, solar thermal, photovoltaics, emergency power.</p>
          <span class="arrow">→</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/chapter-5" class="card tilt-card reveal reveal-delay-2" data-astro-prefetch>
          <div class="card-glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <span class="n">05</span>
          <h3 class="serif">Energy &amp; Carbon Baseline</h3>
          <p>The town hall's 2025 electricity, heat, costs and CO₂ — measured, calculated, broken down.</p>
          <span class="arrow">→</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/chapter-6" class="card tilt-card reveal reveal-delay-3" data-astro-prefetch>
          <div class="card-glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          <span class="n">06</span>
          <h3 class="serif">Carbon-Reduction Calculator</h3>
          <p>Interactive what-if model — adjust PV and solar-thermal sliders to see CO₂, costs, payback, NPV.</p>
          <span class="arrow">→</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Introduction -->
  <Section chip="Chapter 01" label="Introduction" title="Introduction" id="chapter-1">
    <h3>About the Municipality</h3>
    <p>Oberägeri is a municipality in the Canton of Zug, tucked away in the Ägerital valley at about 724 metres above sea level. It sits right on the northern edge of the Ägerisee, and covers a total area of around 30.0 km². Much of that land remains natural, with forests making up 45.9% of the area (FSO, 2021). As of 2019, the population stood at 6,244 residents, following a steady growth spurt of 14.5% over the last ten years (FSO, 2021). The community is largely German-speaking, and there is a high emphasis on education, with over 76% of the working-age population having finished secondary or higher schooling (FSO, 2021).</p>
    <p>Fast forward to today, and Oberägeri is well-known for its <em>Energiestadt</em> (Energy City) status. First certified on 12 June 2009, the town has consistently improved its energy score increasing it from 64% in 2013 to 70.3% in 2021 (Trägerverein Energiestadt, 2021; Zuger Zeitung, 2021). This shows how sustainability is a central focus of the local government with strategic funding spread across five key areas: energy consulting, Minergie building standards, renewable heating, solar power, and green mobility (Gemeinde Oberägeri, 2024). There are long-term plans in motion to expand local energy networks, or <em>Energieverbunde</em>, to eventually remove fossil fuel reliance completely. It's this local culture of environmental responsibility that provides the backdrop for this study, which looks at energy consumption's effect on carbon and how this can be reduced using alternative power sources.</p>

    <div class="intro-image reveal-scale">
      <img src="/Oberaegeri_Luftbild2.jpg" alt="Aerial view of Oberägeri" />
      <span class="caption">Oberägeri, Canton Zug — Ägerital valley</span>
    </div>

    <h3>About the Project</h3>
    <p>The transition towards sustainable energy systems is a paramount challenge for contemporary municipal administrations. As public institutions, municipalities such as Oberägeri serve as critical catalysts for regional climate protection and carbon neutrality. This research focuses on the Oberägeri Town hall, examining the potential for systematic energy optimization within administrative operational frameworks. The energy and carbon baseline underpinning this study draws on audited consumption data and operational details provided directly by the municipal administration (Klauz, 2026). By integrating technical efficiency measures with strategic carbon reduction protocols, this study aims to define a replicable model for municipal sustainability. The following sections outline the methodology, state analysis, and specific technological alternatives designed to minimize the ecological footprint of public buildings while maintaining fiscal responsibility and service excellence.</p>
  </Section>

  <!-- Project Objectives -->
  <Section chip="Chapter 02" label="Objectives" title="Project Objectives" id="chapter-2">
    <ol class="objectives">
      <li class="obj-item reveal">
        <span class="obj-n">01</span>
        <p>Establish a verified energy and CO₂ baseline for the Rathaus using audited data on electricity, district heat, hot water, and emergency generator consumption (Klauz, 2026).</p>
      </li>
      <li class="obj-item reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <span class="obj-n">02</span>
        <p>Evaluate three reduction approaches: rooftop photovoltaic generation, solar thermal heating, and sustainable generator solution.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="obj-item reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <span class="obj-n">03</span>
        <p>Compare approaches on CO₂ savings, life-cycle costs, and financial viability within Swiss municipal constraints.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="obj-item reveal reveal-delay-3">
        <span class="obj-n">04</span>
        <p>Create a prioritised carbon-reduction roadmap for Oberägeri's municipal administration.</p>
      </li>
    </ol>

  </Section>

  <!-- Methodology -->
  <Section chip="Chapter 03" label="Method" title="Methodology" id="chapter-3">
    <div class="method-grid">
      <div class="method-card tilt-card reveal">
        <div class="card-glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <h4>Literature Research</h4>
        <p>A targeted literature review covers four domains relevant to the case: (1) Swiss multi-level sustainability governance and the Energiestadt label; (2) Standards for energy-efficiency in public buildings and the retrofit performance gap (SIA 380/1, MuKEn, Minergie); (3) Carbon-and-cost case for renewable generation; and (4) Photovoltaic and solar-thermal performance together with emergency-power system design.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="method-card tilt-card reveal reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="card-glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <h4>Data Collection</h4>
        <p>Primary consumption data was obtained through direct correspondence with the Verwaltungsleiter of Oberägeri, Alexander Klauz. The dataset includes audited annual electricity consumption for 2024 (37,460 kWh) and 2025 (41,150 kWh) split into administrative and residential meters, the WWZ "WasserSonneStrom" tariff mix (80 % hydropower, 20 % PV), the wood-chip Wärmeverbund supplying district heat, hot-water demand (≈ 507 m³ in 2025) and the parameters of the diesel Krisenstab generator. The municipal budget process and the CHF 200'000 Finanzkompetenz threshold were also documented to anchor the financial analysis.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="method-card tilt-card reveal reveal-delay-2">
        <div class="card-glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <h4>Scenario Analysis</h4>
        <p>A baseline CO₂ footprint is calculated using KBOB emission factors (≈ 0.019 kgCO₂eq/kWh for the WWZ electricity mix and ≈ 0.025 kgCO₂eq/kWh for wood-chip district heat). Two intervention scenarios, rooftop PV and PV heating, are then modelled against this baseline, comparing CO₂ savings, investment cost relative to the Finanzkompetenz threshold, and economic viability over a 25-year horizon. The diesel generator is assessed separately because the Krisenstab requires unlimited-duration backup, which constrains replacement options.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </Section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta">
    <div class="container cta-inner reveal">
      <div>
        <span class="lbl">Try the live tool</span>
        <h2 class="serif">Open the carbon-reduction calculator</h2>
      </div>
      <a href="/chapter-6" class="btn" data-astro-prefetch>Launch calculator →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
  /* ── Stats strip ── */
  .stats-strip{
    padding:clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px) 0;
    border-bottom:1px solid rgba(230,224,210,0.5);
    background:rgba(250,250,247,0.4);
    backdrop-filter:blur(8px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter:blur(8px);
  }
  .stats-grid{
    display:grid;
    grid-template-columns:repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap:clamp(16px, 3vw, 40px);
  }
  @media(max-width:640px){.stats-grid{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}}
  .stat{
    display:flex;
    flex-direction:column;
    align-items:flex-start;
    gap:4px;
    padding:0 clamp(12px,2vw,24px);
    border-left:2px solid var(--line);
  }
  .stat:first-child{border-left:none;padding-left:0}
  .stat-n{
    font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;
    font-size:clamp(32px, 4vw, 52px);
    font-weight:400;
    color:var(--ink);
    line-height:1;
    letter-spacing:-0.02em;
  }
  .stat-unit{
    font-size:14px;
    color:var(--moss);
    font-weight:500;
    margin-left:2px;
    align-self:flex-end;
    padding-bottom:6px;
  }
  .stat-label{
    font-size:11px;
    letter-spacing:.2em;
    text-transform:uppercase;
    color:var(--mute);
    font-weight:400;
    margin-top:4px;
  }

  /* ── Overview ── */
  .overview{
    padding:clamp(48px, 7vw, 80px) 0;
  }
  .overview-inner{
    display:grid;
    grid-template-columns:160px 1fr;
    gap:clamp(24px, 4vw, 56px);
    align-items:start;
  }
  @media(max-width:680px){.overview-inner{grid-template-columns:1fr;gap:12px}}
  .overview-label{
    font-size:11px;
    letter-spacing:.28em;
    text-transform:uppercase;
    color:var(--moss);
    font-weight:500;
    padding-top:6px;
  }
  .overview-body{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:20px}
  .overview-text{
    font-size:clamp(19px, 2.2vw, 24px);
    line-height:1.75;
    color:var(--ink-soft);
    margin:0;
    font-weight:300;
    max-width:68ch;
  }
  .overview-text em{font-style:italic;color:var(--ink)}

  /* ── Chapter index ── */
  .chapter-index{
    padding:clamp(48px, 7vw, 80px) 0;
    border-top:1px solid rgba(230,224,210,0.5);
  }
  .grid{
    display:grid;
    grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit, minmax(260px, 1fr));
    gap:clamp(16px, 2vw, 24px);
  }
  .card{
    position:relative;
    padding:36px 32px 32px;
    background:rgba(250,250,247,0.55);
    backdrop-filter:saturate(180%) blur(18px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter:saturate(180%) blur(18px);
    border:1px solid rgba(230,224,210,0.6);
    border-radius:4px;
    color:inherit;
    overflow:hidden;
    transition:transform 0.25s var(--ease-out), box-shadow 0.25s var(--ease-out), border-color 0.25s;
    transform-style:preserve-3d;
    will-change:transform;
  }
  .card-glow{
    position:absolute;
    inset:0;
    background:radial-gradient(600px circle at var(--mouse-x,50%) var(--mouse-y,50%),
      rgba(59,90,63,0.08), transparent 50%);
    opacity:0;
    transition:opacity 0.4s;
    pointer-events:none;
    border-radius:inherit;
  }
  .card:hover .card-glow{opacity:1}
  .card:hover{
    box-shadow:0 20px 50px rgba(26,34,38,0.1);
    border-color:rgba(94,125,99,0.4);
  }
  .card > *{position:relative;z-index:1}
  .n{
    display:block;
    font-size:11px;
    letter-spacing:.32em;
    color:var(--moss);
    font-weight:500;
    margin-bottom:20px;
  }
  .card h3{
    font-size:26px;
    line-height:1.2;
    margin:0 0 14px;
    color:var(--ink);
  }
  .card p{
    font-size:14px;
    line-height:1.75;
    color:var(--ink-soft);
    margin:0 0 32px;
    font-weight:300;
  }
  .arrow{
    font-size:22px;
    color:var(--moss);
    transition:transform 0.35s var(--ease-out);
    display:inline-block;
  }
  .card:hover .arrow{transform:translateX(8px)}

  /* ── Objectives ── */
  .objectives{
    list-style:none;margin:0;padding:0;
  }
  .obj-item{
    display:grid;
    grid-template-columns:64px 1fr;
    gap:24px;
    align-items:start;
    padding:28px 16px;
    border-bottom:1px solid rgba(230,224,210,0.5);
    border-radius:4px;
    transition:background 0.3s var(--ease-out);
    cursor:default;
  }
  .obj-item:last-child{border-bottom:none}
  .obj-item:hover{background:rgba(59,90,63,0.04)}
  .obj-n{
    font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif;
    font-size:40px;
    font-weight:400;
    color:rgba(230,224,210,0.8);
    line-height:1;
    padding-top:2px;
    transition:color 0.3s;
  }
  .obj-item:hover .obj-n{color:var(--moss-2)}
  .objectives p{
    font-size:clamp(15px,1.6vw,17px) !important;
    line-height:1.8 !important;
    color:var(--ink-soft) !important;
    margin:0 !important;
    font-weight:300 !important;
    max-width:64ch !important;
  }

  /* ── Methodology ── */
  .method-grid{
    display:grid;
    grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px,1fr));
    gap:clamp(16px,2vw,24px);
    margin-bottom:36px;
  }
  .method-card{
    position:relative;
    padding:32px 28px;
    background:rgba(250,250,247,0.55);
    backdrop-filter:saturate(180%) blur(18px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter:saturate(180%) blur(18px);
    border:1px solid rgba(230,224,210,0.6);
    border-radius:4px;
    overflow:hidden;
    transition:transform 0.25s var(--ease-out), box-shadow 0.25s var(--ease-out), border-color 0.25s;
    transform-style:preserve-3d;
    will-change:transform;
  }
  .method-card:hover{
    box-shadow:0 16px 40px rgba(26,34,38,0.1);
    border-color:rgba(94,125,99,0.4);
  }
  .method-card > *{position:relative;z-index:1}
  .method-card h4{
    font-family:'Inter',sans-serif;
    font-size:11px;
    letter-spacing:.22em;
    text-transform:uppercase;
    color:var(--chip);
    font-weight:600;
    margin:0 0 16px;
  }
  .method-card p{
    font-size:14px !important;
    line-height:1.75 !important;
    color:var(--ink-soft) !important;
    margin:0 !important;
    font-weight:300 !important;
  }

  /* ── Intro image (landing page) ── */
  .intro-image{
    margin:28px 0 36px;
    border-radius:4px;
    overflow:hidden;
  }
  .intro-image img{
    width:100%;
    height:320px;
    object-fit:cover;
    display:block;
    transition:transform 0.6s var(--ease-out);
  }
  .intro-image:hover img{transform:scale(1.02)}
  .caption{
    display:block;
    margin-top:10px;
    font-size:11px;
    letter-spacing:.14em;
    text-transform:uppercase;
    color:var(--mute);
    font-weight:400;
  }

  /* ── CTA ── */
  .cta{
    background:var(--ink);
    padding:clamp(80px,12vw,140px) 0;
    color:var(--paper);
  }
  .cta-inner{
    display:flex;
    justify-content:space-between;
    align-items:center;
    flex-wrap:wrap;
    gap:40px;
  }
  .cta .lbl{
    font-size:11px;
    letter-spacing:.32em;
    text-transform:uppercase;
    color:var(--accent);
    font-weight:500;
  }
  .cta h2{
    font-size:clamp(28px,4vw,48px);
    line-height:1.15;
    font-weight:400;
    margin:14px 0 0;
    letter-spacing:-0.015em;
    max-width:18ch;
    color:#fff;
  }
  .btn{
    display:inline-block;
    padding:18px 40px;
    background:var(--accent);
    color:var(--ink);
    font-size:13px;
    letter-spacing:.16em;
    text-transform:uppercase;
    font-weight:500;
    transition:all 0.3s var(--ease-out);
    border-radius:2px;
    white-space:nowrap;
  }
  .btn:hover{
    background:#fff;
    transform:translateY(-3px);
    box-shadow:0 16px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.25);
  }
</style>

<script>
  function initPage() {
    // ── Animated counters ──
    const counters = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('[data-target]');
    const counterObs = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
      entries.forEach((entry) => {
        if (!entry.isIntersecting) return;
        const el = entry.target as HTMLElement;
        const target = parseInt(el.dataset.target ?? '0', 10);
        const isDecimal = 'decimal' in el.dataset;
        const duration = 1800;
        let start: number | null = null;
        const step = (ts: number) => {
          if (!start) start = ts;
          const p = Math.min((ts - start) / duration, 1);
          const eased = 1 - Math.pow(1 - p, 3);
          const val = eased * target;
          el.textContent = isDecimal
            ? (val / 10).toFixed(1)
            : Math.round(val).toLocaleString('de-CH');
          if (p < 1) requestAnimationFrame(step);
        };
        requestAnimationFrame(step);
        counterObs.unobserve(el);
      });
    }, { threshold: 0.5 });
    counters.forEach((el) => counterObs.observe(el));

    // ── Card tilt + spotlight glow ──
    const tiltCards = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.tilt-card');
    tiltCards.forEach((card) => {
      const glow = card.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.card-glow');

      card.addEventListener('mousemove', (e: MouseEvent) => {
        const rect = card.getBoundingClientRect();
        const x = e.clientX - rect.left;
        const y = e.clientY - rect.top;
        const cx = rect.width / 2;
        const cy = rect.height / 2;
        const rx = ((y - cy) / cy) * -6;
        const ry = ((x - cx) / cx) * 6;
        card.style.transform = `perspective(800px) rotateX(${rx}deg) rotateY(${ry}deg) translateY(-4px)`;
        if (glow) {
          glow.style.setProperty('--mouse-x', x + 'px');
          glow.style.setProperty('--mouse-y', y + 'px');
        }
      });

      card.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => {
        card.style.transform = '';
        card.style.transition = 'transform 0.5s var(--ease-out), box-shadow 0.25s, border-color 0.25s';
        setTimeout(() => { card.style.transition = ''; }, 500);
      });
    });
  }

  initPage();
  document.addEventListener('astro:after-swap', initPage);
</script>
